body_text.text:
The mean age of the 76 patients was 4.7 years (standard deviation, ±3.9 years). Respiratory microorganisms were detected in 74 (97%) of our patients. Viruses were found in 55 (72%) and bacteria in 69 (91%) of the studied children. Proportions of microbiological findings are shown in Fig. 1
. One child had six microorganisms (three bacteria and three viruses) simultaneously detected (Fig. 2
) and, altogether, seven children had two or three bacteria with two or three viruses co-detected (Table 2
).
